items.name: Virile Motion
items.description:
If you'd like to buy me a beer or coffee! 🍺☕

This model is my third merge and has been fine-tuned in order to produce convincing male-focused gens without the need for Loras, even with simple prompts.

This model attempts to explore a more "animated" look in the style of Disney/Pixar movies.

It is built upon my two previous merges, Virile Fusion and Virile Reality, however it is not a replacement and only aims at offering a different style, which could not be achieved by my two other models.

In the end, whichever model you decide to use is a matter of preference.

Models included in the merge are:

  • Virile Fusion

  • Disney Pixar Cartoon type B

Loras included in the merge are:

  • Penis LoRA

  • Tgirls

  • Anime penis LORA

While the model has been crafted to be male-centric, it also allows for the generation of other types of characters (including females) as well as landscapes, or objects.

Recommended settings for good gens (Automatic1111):

  • Sampling Method: Euler A

  • Sampling Steps: 40

  • Hires. fix On

  • Upscaler: R-ESRGAN 4x+

  • Hires Steps: 20

  • Denoising Strength: 0.5

  • Upscale: 1.7/2.0

  • Width: 512

  • Height: 768

  • CFG Scale: 5

I also highly recommend using After Detailer for faces, using the "mediapipe_face_mesh" model.

VAE-wise, I would advise to use the following one: vae-ft-mse-840000-ema-pruned

I would also like to mention and thank the Unstable Diffusion Discord Server's #men-only community who helped me learn a lot. Some of the gens done with the model include their prompts.

Extensions -> available -> load from -> additional networks

Restart webui

place lora into stable-diffusion-webui\extensions\sd-webui-additional-networks\models\lora

items.name: Ai Prompt Studio
items.description:
Introducing Ai Prompt Studio:

The Workflow Enhancement for Prompt Engineering

NOTE: This tool does not generate alone but aids a prompt engineer to manage, save and improve the workflows of prompt engineering.

Development Roadmap / Release Details: https://poda.io/b/UZB49kTtem56KGYWg76P

Discord: https://discord.gg/Sv55Xgguw6

In the rapidly evolving field of Prompt Engineering, having the right tools at your disposal is crucial for maintaining productivity. That's where Ai Prompt Studio comes in - an agnostic tool designed to empower Prompt Engineers regardless of the specific AI tool they specialize in.


Why Ai Prompt Studio?

In the realm of prompt engineering, tools are constantly evolving at an unprecedented pace. The complexity of prompt engineering makes it humanly impossible to maximize efficiency without careful planning, experimentation, iteration, and avoiding common pitfalls.

That's why I'm thrilled to present Ai Prompt Studio, a solution tailored to meet the needs of professional Prompt Engineers. Whether you're working with images, text, audio, video, or 3D generation, Ai Prompt Studio has got you covered.

Unlike other applications that fall short in organizing and strategizing prompts, Ai Prompt Studio is meticulously crafted to cater to the specific requirements of Prompt Engineers. As a future Prompt Engineer myself, I recognized the need for a universal tool that allows practitioners of all skill levels to work seamlessly across various AI generators, without the need to restart the learning process with each new tool.

The best part? Ai Prompt Studio is available now, and it's completely free for everyone. Developed in phases, it will encompass all types of AI generator functionalities, including Images, Text, Audio, Video, and 3D models. Currently, I'm focusing on laying the foundation with Images, as it encompasses many overlapping variables from other generation types.

Key Features to Boost Your Productivity:

1. Add prompts, images, and models effortlessly.

2. Prompt Linking: Connect any prompt to any image or model seamlessly.

3. Deep Filtering: Explore the intricate relationships between an unlimited number of prompts, models, and images in any direction you desire.

4. Download model details for local storage: Safeguard critical information about a model, even if it gets removed from the provider.

5. Browse CivitAi.com directly within the tool for a streamlined experience.

6. View image metadata to gain valuable insights.

7. Collect, Compare, and Organize all of your generated images efficiently.

8. Modular window layout: Enjoy the flexibility of arranging and customizing the tool's interface according to your preferences.

9. Prompt Blocks: Ai Prompt Studio automatically tracks keywords and phrases used in your prompts, allowing for statistical analysis and easy retrieval of images resulting from specific prompts.

As the developer of Ai Prompt Studio, I wholeheartedly invite you to try this powerful tool. Remember, it's free for everyone. If you find it useful or have any feedback, please don't hesitate to reach out to me through Discord or any platform of your choice.

Experience the future of Prompt Engineering with Ai Prompt Studio today!

items.description:
If there are any images you generate with this LORA which you particularly like, please do share them below. I'd really appreciate understanding how it's used and how it performs. Thanks!

Batman from the Burton-verse, aka Batman '89, aka the GOAT.

I've made this model to more or less fulfill a childhood fantasy: more films with Michael Keaton as Bruce Wayne set in the dark, dank world of Burton's (very British) Gotham.

  • The SD1.5 model was trained on Realistic Vision 2.0

  • The SDXL model was trained on SDXL base

1992's sequel to Batman, Batman Returns, featured a different suit and I may turn my hand to that later and create a separate model.

items.name: Ilya Kuvshinov - Artist Style
items.description:
Ilya Kuvshinov - Artist Style 🎨

These LoRAs explores multiple artstyles of the extremely talented artist Ilya Kuvshinov, if by any chance you dont know them yet you should really check out their artworks at artstation or instagram.

Style1: hard shaded anime

Style2: semi realistic faces and proportions

Style3: flat high contrast monochrome

Usage Tips :

  • regular use is at the weight of 0.8 to 1

  • No need for activation word but adding ilyast1orilyast2orilyast3(depending on what LoRA ur using ) to the prompt will force the image elements toward subjects (NSFW) covered by the artist , and also gives the LoRA a bit more influence but might break other LoRAs.

Fun Tips :

  • adding "realistic" works well with Style2

Samples settings :

  • Checkpoints: Anything 5 , Anylora

  • Steps : 22-28

  • Sampler : DPM++ 2M

  • ClipSkip : 2

have fun and consider rating ⭐

items.name: Bob Ross Painting Style
items.description:
If you like my contributions to the community, please consider Buying Me A Coffee or check out my other sites on AllMyLinks

TRAINING INFO

  • Trained on 32 images

  • Trained at 1024 resolution

RECOMMENDED SETTINGS

TXT2IMG - A weight of 1 works just fine and will yield some interesting results, but I recommend a weight of 0.4-0.7 for more flexibility while still keeping Bob's style.

PROMPTS - I highly recommend using prompts that describe the landscape you want. Simply adding the lora to your prompts won't yield optimal results. For a full list of the prompts/captions used for training, check the Lora file's metadata in your webgui.

items.name: PhantomIXRow - Artist Style
items.description:
Description

First LORA training.

Trying to better learn how the training process works / doesn't work.

Heavily influenced by PhantomIXRow's artstyle - There is also a Model that you can use instead - if you really strictly want that art style.

Prompting Info

  • Works well with any variety of models for different effects, try anime or western.

  • No specific prompts really required can do really anything you want but is heavily impacted by the underlying Model.

  • All my sample images are at 1.0 strength, feel free to down rank intensity as needed.

  • None of the samples leverage any other LORA's / Hypernetworks / or any clean up edits, tried to keep prompts simple.

Credits

Original Artist

  • Credit to the original artist PhantomIXRow for influencing the dataset

  • Credit to Cosk, who produced the original dataset I used for testing

Support me on Ko-Fi!

I ended up trying a different approach of taking an existing lactation model and training some additional concepts (e.g. stock images of pure honey) to get the viscosity correct.

I'm also planning on attempting other... "beverages."

items.name: Pissmouth - Piss drinking humiliation
items.description:
Piss drinking humiliation. Trained for photorealistic models but seems to work a bit with others.

The dicks don't look great.

Examples from ICBINP and AOM

Start with 1.0 weight. Good starting prompt:

photo of woman being a pissmouth, on her knees, a man is peeing into her mouth <lora:pissmouth_v1:1.0>

Adding other LORAs with low weight and no triggers (like POV Fellatio) can help a lot
